.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-git_sweep \- Preview and clean up a Git repository by removing merged branches, clearing stashes, sweeping untracked build artifacts, and compressing object storage with `git gc`.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility git_sweep
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Preview and clean up a Git repository by removing merged branches, clearing stashes, sweeping untracked build artifacts, and compressing object storage with `git gc`.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBMerged branch detection\fP — finds fully merged local and remote branches that are safe to delete
.IP \(bu 4
\fBStash cleanup\fP — lists and optionally clears all stashes in the repository
.IP \(bu 4
\fBArtifact sweep\fP — previews and removes untracked build files using \fCgit clean -fdx\fP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBObject compression\fP — runs \fCgit gc --prune=now\fP to compact the repository's object storage
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSafe by default\fP — all destructive actions require explicit confirmation before anything is changed
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments shows a full preview then prompts for each action
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _git_sweep/_git_sweep.sh

bash _git_sweep/_git_sweep.sh --repo ~/projects/myapp

bash _git_sweep/_git_sweep.sh --repo . --delete-merged-local --apply

bash _git_sweep/_git_sweep.sh --repo . --delete-merged-local --delete-merged-remote --apply

bash _git_sweep/_git_sweep.sh --repo . --gc --apply

bash _git_sweep/_git_sweep.sh --repo . --delete-merged-local --clean-artifacts --gc --apply
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fC--repo DIR\fP   |   Repository directory to operate on (default: \fC.\fP)
\fC--delete-merged-local\fP   |   Delete fully merged local branches
\fC--delete-merged-remote\fP   |   Delete fully merged remote branches from \fCorigin\fP
\fC--drop-stashes\fP   |   Clear all git stashes
\fC--clean-artifacts\fP   |   Remove untracked build files with \fCgit clean -fdx\fP
\fC--gc\fP   |   Run \fCgit gc --prune=now\fP to compress object storage
\fC--apply\fP   |   Execute selected actions (nothing is changed without this flag)
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH WHAT QUALIFIES AS A MERGED BRANCH
.PP
The tool compares branches against the repository's default branch, which is detected automatically in this order:
.PP
.IP \(em 4
\fCorigin/HEAD\fP symbolic ref
.IP \(em 4
First match among \fCmain\fP, \fCmaster\fP, \fCtrunk\fP
.IP \(em 4
Current checked-out branch as fallback
.PP
Only branches fully contained in the default branch's history are listed as candidates. The default branch itself, \fCmain\fP, \fCmaster\fP, and \fCtrunk\fP are always excluded from deletion regardless of merge status.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH PREVIEW OUTPUT
.PP
Running in interactive mode always shows a full preview before any prompts:
.PP
.EX
  Merged local branches
  ------------------------------------------------
  • feat/login-page
  • fix/typo-in-readme

  Merged remote branches
  ------------------------------------------------
  (none found)

  Git stashes
  ------------------------------------------------
  • stash@{0}: WIP on main: abc1234 some message

  Untracked build artifacts preview
  ------------------------------------------------
  • Would remove dist/
  • Would remove node_modules/.cache/
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   Not a git repository, or unknown option passed
